Inviting d4, in order to play Bg4, and press c3 with Ne4, etc. The "usual, smooth, nice black  plan".
A step ahead. Now Qe2 gives black just a painful defence.
A step ahead. Now Qe2 gives black just a painful defence.
The fish bite the worm... I hope. But first, I have to take advantage from what I was playing for..
With check.
Keeping the Q for future action.
With several threats, most of them well met by... (dxf can currently be played, BxN+, bxc3, Ne4, annoying...)
I have to take urgent care of the e column, and be aware of the very dangerous Ng5 by white. So I can't just go on normally, castling, Re1, and the Q has no good square to go to.
A thret is a threat.
A thret is a threat.
A thret is a threat.

Now, Bf4 seems good, but in fact black gets very few compensation if ever Ng3 is allowed (NxRf1). On the other side, cxd5 would leave my N without a pawn's support. White will try to move Nf3 in order to be able to kick it with f3, so my Royalties must be guarded soon. I can't count on Be6 if g5 is not protected by a pawn.
Keep the central pawn. Any white's incursion on g5 is now parried with f6.
Of course. I can castle, but then Bd3 and my N will be pinned against the Q and... central disaster for me.
I hope this was the exact one here.
White can attack with c4, to which I plan to play Qc7, pinning the pawn on the Q.

I can go for a drastic Re8, and white will have had a lot of ways to go on with the attack. On the other side, this move would have left my R undefended on e8, and my Q must be free to go. I have a serious developement problem, but I have to find the way to survive.

This leaves complete entry to g5, but I think that Qc7, again, compensates it, while minor white pieces, alone, can do no harm... (maybe!). On the other side, the obvious danger now is white moves the N so to be able to pay f3.
White chooses another way: Ba3. Not the stronges move, as for...
With a threat on c3. I know I'm "lost" but it's up to my opponent to show it. For the time going, I know that no one of my defences will work, but white has to be very accurate.
Re8 self-pinned my N.

That's the move... but it also gives me tempo to come, just in time...
